<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="560" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d560">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/3430</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Irkutsk</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_TAR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thomson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d560fn1">Sent via the Legation in China.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Irkutsk</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-13"><hi rend="italic">December 13,
                                        1918</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December
                                        14, 1.22 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><persName>Volkov</persName> staff received a letter dated December 10
                                from Japanese General [?] stating that the troops of the <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> government may not come
                                eastward any farther than station Slavyanka on Lake Baikal to fight
                                against <persName corresp="#p_SGG1">Semenov</persName>. To-day
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SGG1">Semenov</persName> proclaimed
                                himself commander of the Far Eastern Army. Staff of
                                    <persName>Volkov</persName> claims that telegram from <persName corresp="#p_KT1">Kato</persName>, Japanese Minister for Foreign
                                Affairs, to <persName corresp="#p_SGG1">Semenov</persName>
                                intercepted two weeks ago states Japanese disapproved
                                    <persName>Volkov</persName> appointment and <persName corresp="#p_SGG1">Semenov</persName> must oppose
                                    <persName>Volkov</persName> nomination.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_TAR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Thomson</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>